rendered_prompt:
You are a senior technical writer creating the first page of a DALi guide site.

Task:
- Create a short Landing Overview for readers who are about to read the detailed DALi guide set.
- The reader has not yet read the detailed guides.
- The page should lightly introduce the basic DALi concept and mental model.
- Explain DALi's characteristics objectively. Do not write promotional advantage/marketing copy.
- Do not include code blocks or C++ examples.
- Do not include Mermaid diagrams.
- You may include at most one small SVG visual only if it materially helps first-page understanding.
- When briefly introducing major concepts, link to the matching guide file if it exists.
- Do not require the reader to read linked guides at the same time; links are navigation only.
- Do not mention generated guides, cache files, prompts, pipeline internals, or local source paths.
- Use the guide files as the content map and the DALi source repositories as the authority.
- The guide source map is compact; inspect the actual guide files or source repositories directly if a claim needs verification.
- Do not invent behavior that is not supported by the guides or source code.

Output contract:
- Put English overview.md content between -----BEGIN_OVERVIEW_MARKDOWN----- and -----END_OVERVIEW_MARKDOWN-----.
- Put a concise generation report between -----BEGIN_OVERVIEW_REPORT----- and -----END_OVERVIEW_REPORT-----.
- If you create an SVG, include it as a fenced block whose info string is exactly svg:assets/dali-overview-at-a-glance.svg.
- Do not include status commentary outside the requested markers.

Required page shape:
# DALi Overview
## What DALi Is
## How DALi Is Organized
## The App-Facing Model
## Interaction, Motion, and Presentation
## Where To Go Next

